==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Platinoid
<hw>Plat"i*noid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An alloy of
German silver containing tungsten; -- used for forming electrical
resistance coils and standards.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Platinotype</ent>⟦br⟧
